         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">6/9/87. ¶  ¶ Allow me, dear Mr Maiden, to send to  ¶ you ¶  the money-order of £5, as a subsidy for Mr Baeuerlen during August. ¶  As you have anyhow to send him funds from time to time, my addition t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.09.06b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Maiden</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MRS 202/96/277, Powerhouse Museum, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is stamped and annotated: '<seg>THE TECHNOLOGICAL MUSEUM SYDNEY No. </seg>277<seg> RECEIVED SEP 7 1887</seg> Ansd. 8/9' and '<seg>SUBMITTED SEP 14 1887 TO THE TRUSTEES</seg>'. See J. Maiden to M, 8 September 1884.</p>
               </note>6/9/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me, dear Mr Maiden, to send to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> the money-order of £5, as a subsidy for Mr Baeuerlen during August.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">See also M to J. Maiden, 7 September 1887 (in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>87-09-07a).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> As you have anyhow to send him funds from time to time, my addition to his travelling-resources might as well or better go with yours; indeed you are in a better position to forward to him at the earliest time and to the best adress, than myself. I <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">did</hi>
               </seg> send him in due time the July subsidy of £5 in a money order to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Wilcannia</hi>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> trusting that he will get it cashed further N. W.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>His success so far as the phytography of N.S.W. is concerned depend on two points.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1, that he <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mainly</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">timely</hi>
               </seg> operates in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">remotest</hi>
               </seg> N.W. corner of N.S.W., as repeatedly pointed out to him at the outset.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2, that he collects also all <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">aquatic</hi>
               </seg> p<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">lants</hi>
               </seg> and particularly also <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all minute</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">annuals</hi>
               </seg>, even if shrivelled up. Among these will be most novelty for N.S.W. and indeed for general science also.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I still hope, that you and your friends get the path to the summit of Mt Seaview<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW; see M to the Linnean Society of New South Wales, March 1887 (in this edition as 87-03-00c).</p>
               </note> out timely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">B. ought to operate mainly in the Poole district beyond Milparinka.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW. B. … Milparinka <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is written on the back of the envelope.</seg> On the front of the envelope is: '<seg>On Her Majesty's <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Service.</seg> J. H. Maiden Esqr FRGS. Curator of the technologic Museun, <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Sydney</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Government Botanist</seg>
                     <seg>, Melbourne</seg>, 6/9/<seg>18</seg>87.'</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
